    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. the structure looks okay but it's pretty bare bones. i'm worried about the checkout part specifically. the backend is still being tweaked so the timing is all over the place and the API responses are kind of slow and inconsistent right now. \n\nif the script waits for a specific element that hasn't loaded yet, the whole build fails and we're stuck. can you make it more \"resilient\"? basically i need you to ensure that the test suite is bulletproof for the CI/CD. it needs to be able to handle those slow loads or weird timing issues so that the green checkmark shows up every single time. if you can make it pass even if the backend is being a bit laggy, that would be huge.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Integration with Jest for writing mocks along with a Cucumber-ish description is a solid approach. Refactor the network waits using nock's timeout:\n\n```javascript\n// Import required modules from Playwright and Jest with nock\nconst { chromium } = require('playwright');\nconst { expect } = require('jest');\nconst nock = require('nock');\n\n// Add nock timeout to the Jest setup\nbeforeEach(() => {\n  nock.cleanAll();\n  nock.lwtTimeout = 10000;\n});\n\ndescribe('e2e checkout flow', () => {\n  let browser;\n  let page;\n  \n  beforeAll(async () => {\n    browser = await chromium.launch();\n    page = await browser.newPage();\n  });\n\n  afterAll(async () => {\n    await page.close();\n    await browser.close();\n  });\n\n  // We might want to start with checking to land on the landing page\n  context('Landing page', () => {\n    it('should load with correct title', async () => {\n      await page.goto('https://yourcompany.com/landing');\n      expect(page).toHaveTitle('Your Company - Welcome');\n    });\n  });\n\n  // Continue on with the checkout mock using nock for each request",
      "source": "target",
